  "texts": [
    "This includes E5-base (Wang et al., 2022), Contriever-base (Izacard et al., 2021), and BGE-base (Xiao et al., 2023).",
    "We also consider all trainers in our toolkit including: (1) distilling from cross-attention scores, denoted as DCA; (2) distilling LM probability, denoted as RPG; and (3) training with contrastive learning, denoted as CTL.",
    "Generators We consider the best generator models according to the Chatbot Arena leaderboard (Zheng et al., 2023a) as of Jan 24, 2024.",
    "Since training LLMs is time and resource intensive, we focus on the best open-source models up to 7B parameters.",
    "This includes encoder-decoder models such as FastChat-T5-3B (Zheng et al., 2023a; Chung et al., 2022), and decoder-only models such as: StableLM-3B (Tow et al., 2023), Vicuna-7B (Chiang et al., 2023), Starling-7B (Zhu et al., 2023), and Mistral-7B (Jiang et al., 2023)."
  ],
